This paper analyzes the behavior of bidders in quasi-proportional auctions, which is a topic in game theory and mechanism design. Therefore, cs.GT (Game Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of exponential weight functions, which is a topic in machine learning and optimization, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also involves mathematical analysis and modeling, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper is related to auction theory and market design, which could fall under cs.EC (Economics and Computation).
